setInterval calls a function or evaluates an expression at specified intervals (milliseconds)
clearInterval (stops the setInterval from calling the function√ü)


setTimeout calls a function after a speicifed number of seconds
    if you need to repeat the execution, use setInterval

clearTimeout  Prevent the function set with the setTimeout() to execute. also: 
    The clearTimeout() method clears a timer set with the setTimeout() method.

